cs.DL, cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY

The paper discusses a decentralized approach to publishing and archiving scientific data, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it deals with the dissemination and archiving of digital content. cs.DB (Databases) is also relevant as the paper proposes a novel way to store and retrieve scientific datasets. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper discusses methods for retrieving and recombining datasets. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as the proposed system is a network of servers that store and share data. Finally, cs.CY (Computers and Society) is relevant as the paper discusses the societal implications of a decentralized approach to scientific publishing.
